---- MODULE HDiskSynod ----- (* Assuming a simple bank account scenario *)  === Module definition and comments ====    \* Last modified Sat Jan 26 15:47 CET by tthai    == Initialization of Constants, Variables ==      CONSTANTS NotAnInput = 0;       VARIABLES inp = [NotAninput];
  === Operations Definition ====    Deposit(bk) ==  /\ b.bal'  = bal + Amount  \* deposit operation    == Assuming an amount is a constant and available globally ==      Withdrawal (Amount, BK') =>       IF Balance >= AMOUNT THEN          [BAL = BALESCONS - amnt]
        ELSE         (* No action or error *)           FALSE;  === State Transition ====    NextState ==  /\ inp' ∈ {NotAnInput, Deposit(inpt), Withdrawal (Amount)} ==     IF bk.bal =0 THEN       [bk1] BAL =  BALESCONS - amnt;
        ELSE      (* No action or error *)             FALSE ;  === Specification Definition ====    SPECIFICATION ==  /\ InitState ∧ []BK' ==> Nextstate \* Initial state and transition relation between states.     [BALES = BALESCONS] AND inpt = 0;
==== Configuration for TLC ======= (* The configuration tells the ModelChecker how to explore our model *)  === Constants Definition ====    CONSTANTS Amount, Balescons ==  /\ Positive Reals , NonEmptySetofReal >  BALESCONS ;     INVARIANTS (bk.bal ≠0) => BAL > |BALES|; (* An account must have a balance greater than the minimum value of bal esc on input *)   ====